// "package-lock.json" is an auto-generated file that locks
// the exact versions of dependencies and ensures consistent
// and reliable installations across different environments.

// Key features of "package-lock.json":

// 1. Version Locking: It locks the exact versions of all
//    dependencies and their sub-dependencies, ensuring that
//    the same versions are installed every time, regardless of
//    updates to the packages.
// 2. Performance: It speeds up the installation process by
//    providing a detailed map of the dependency tree, allowing
//    npm to quickly resolve and install packages.
// 3. Security: By locking dependencies to specific versions, it
//    helps prevent the introduction of breaking changes or
//    vulnerabilities that may arise from newer versions of
//    packages.

// The "package-lock.json" file is automatically generated when
// you run `npm install` and should be committed to version
// control to ensure that all team members and deployment
// environments use the same dependency versions.